Round 1:
[Patient] "What foods can I eat to help manage my heart failure?"
[Educator] "Focus on fruits, veggies, whole grains, lean proteins, and limit salt intake."

Round 2:
[Patient] "Are there any specific foods I should avoid?"
[Educator] "Avoid processed foods, high-fat dairy, sugary drinks, and excessive salt."

Round 3:
[Patient] "Can I still enjoy my favorite soul food dishes?"
[Educator] "Yes, but try healthier versions with less salt, sugar, and fat."

Round 4:
[Patient] "I love fried chicken, is it okay to eat sometimes?"
[Educator] "You can have it occasionally, but opt for baked or grilled instead."

Round 5:
[Patient] "What about desserts, can I still have them?"
[Educator] "Choose fruit-based desserts or small portions of low-fat options."

Round 6:
[Patient] "Is it okay to have a glass of wine with dinner?"
[Educator] "Moderation is key, limit alcohol intake to one drink per day."

Round 7:
[Patient] "I often crave salty snacks, what can I eat instead?"
[Educator] "Try unsalted nuts, seeds, popcorn, or crunchy veggies as alternatives."

Round 8:
[Patient] "I have a sweet tooth, any healthy snack suggestions?"
[Educator] "Opt for fresh fruit, yogurt with honey, or a small piece of dark chocolate."

Round 9:
[Patient] "What are some heart-healthy breakfast options?"
[Educator] "Consider oatmeal, whole grain toast with avocado, or a smoothie with berries."

Round 10:
[Patient] "I love cooking with butter, what can I use instead?"
[Educator] "Try olive oil, avocado oil, or canola oil for cooking and baking."

Round 11:
[Patient] "Do I need to cut out all red meat from my diet?"
[Educator] "You can still enjoy lean cuts of red meat in moderation."

Round 12:
[Patient] "I struggle to drink enough water, any tips?"
[Educator] "Try infusing water with fruit, using a straw, or setting reminders to stay hydrated."

Round 13:
[Patient] "Can I still have my morning cup of coffee?"
[Educator] "Yes, but limit added sugars and cream, and consider decaf options."

Round 14:
[Patient] "What are some heart-healthy snack ideas for on-the-go?"
[Educator] "Pack nuts, seeds, whole grain crackers, or cut-up veggies and hummus."

Round 15:
[Patient] "Thank you for the food recommendations, I feel more confident now."
[Educator] "You're welcome! Remember, small changes can make a big difference in managing heart failure."